    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6960" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅσος, ὅσσος</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">how great,
            how much</span>, pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">how many</span>, w. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τόσσος</span> expressed or implied as antec.,
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as great</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as</span>, (<span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as
          much</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as</span>, pl. (<span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as many</span>)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as</span> (quantus, quot); very often the appropriate form
          of <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πᾶς</span> precedes (or is implied) as
          antecedent, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Τρώων ὅσσοι ἄριστοι</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">all</span> the bravest of the Trojans, <i><span class="en">Il. 12.13</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            2.125</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 11.388</span></i>,
          etc.—Neut. as adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅσον, ὅσσον, ὅσον ἔπι, ὅσσον
            τ᾽ ἔπι</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as far as</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 2.616</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.251</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ὅσον ἐς Σκαιὰ̄ς πύλᾱς</span>,
            ‘<span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">only</span> as far as,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            9.354</span></i>; so <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅσον τε</span>, ‘about,’
            <i><span class="en">Od. 9.322</span></i>; w. comp. and sup., ‘by
          how much,’ ‘how far,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 9.160</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.516</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
